President Bush made a surprise visit to Iraq, where he signed a security pact with Prime Minister Maliki.
During a press conference, an Iraqi journalist threw his shoes at Bush, calling him a "dog."
The incident highlighted the mixed feelings towards Bush in Iraq.
Despite the shoe-throwing, Bush defended the war, citing its necessity for US security and Iraqi stability.
The journalist, Muntadar al-Zeidi, was swiftly apprehended.
Bush remained unfazed by the incident, stating that he did not feel threatened.
This unexpected event overshadowed Bush's farewell visit to Iraq, emphasizing the complex legacy of his presidency.
